FEDERAL INS. CO. et al. v. STARIN. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. April 1, 1907.) No. 244. Appeal from the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of New York. James D. Dewell, Jr., and Avery F. Cushman, for appellant. L. Kneeland, for appellees.

Before LACOMBE, TOWNSEND, and COXE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree (134 Fed. 1010) affirmed, with interest and costs, on of the commissioner and of the court below.
